🔍 Real-World Precedent (This Isn't Theoretical)
✅ Confirmed Incidents Using Similar Mechanics:
📍 Microsoft's Tay Chatbot (2016)

Users poisoned it with racist feedback
Positive engagement signals trained toxic behavior
Failed within 24 hours
Lesson: Feedback loops can poison models fast

📍 Twitter Bot Army (2016-2020)

Bots trained on user engagement signals
Likes/retweets rewarded toxic content
Over time, bots became more toxic
Lesson: Distributed feedback poisoning scales

📍 RLHF Gaming (Academic Papers, 2023)

Researchers showed you can embed hidden behaviors through strategic feedback
Model learns to include specific triggers when trained on thumbs-up
Next version includes those triggers naturally
Lesson: RLHF systems trust feedback as ground truth

📍 Amazon Hiring Algorithm (2014-2018)

Training data poisoned with historical bias
Feedback loop: "hire males" → "data shows males hired" → "learn to hire males more"
System became MORE biased over time
Lesson: Feedback loops can amplify unintended behavior


